  "ciliary_role": "Rab8 targets vesicles to the cilium and promotes ciliary membrane elongation. It is activated by Rabin8 (17574030, 22433857). I ctivating Rab8 (GDP- bound state) blocks ciliogenesis and induces BBS phenotypes in zebrafish (17574030). Rab8a, Rab8b and Rab10 work synergistically for ciliogenesis (24213529). Rab8a specifically interacts with cenexin/ODF2, a basal body and microtubule binding protein required for cilium biogenesis (17646400). Regulates the trafficking of rhodopsin in photoreceptors. Interacts with RPGR which regulates its activity and localisation. Involved in polarised trafficking of vesicles from the trans-Golgi network (20631154). Involved in serum-starvation-induced ciliogenesis (32669361)",
